Security Audit Agreement Official Docume.title: Security Audit Agreement
Security Audit Agreement Official Docume.description: This agreement initiated the official security audit for Connected Pakistan. It was mutually signed, granting the audit team necessary permissions. And outlining the agreed-upon scope of the assessment.

Password Policy Official Document 2_3872.title: Password Policy Application Document
Password Policy Official Document 2_3872.description: This custom policy specifies the minimum security requirements for all organizational passwords at Connected Pakistan. It guides users in creating strong credentials to protect accounts and data. Designed for clarity, it is simplified for both technical and non-technical staff to easily understand and adhere to.

Scanning and Enumeration Report Official.title: Scanning and Enumeration Report
Scanning and Enumeration Report Official.description: This report details the comprehensive reconnaissance and enumeration phase, utilizing tools such as Nmap and Nikto. It encompasses findings from both internal and external network scans, identifying hosts, open ports, and services. Providing a foundational understanding of the digital footprint and potential attack vectors.
Scanning and Enumeration Report Official.fileName: Scanning and Enumeration Report Official Document 3_78803108.pdf

Configuration Testing Report Official Do.title: Configuration Testing Report
Configuration Testing Report Official Do.description: This report details the assessment of system and application configurations against security best practices. It validates settings for web servers, firewalls, and software versions for internal and external assets. Ensuring adherence to secure baselines and identifying critical misconfigurations.

Connected Pakistan Network Penetesting O.title: Network Based Pentesting Report
Connected Pakistan Network Penetesting O.description: This report details the simulated attacks against the network infrastructure, including external and internal segments.Utilizing tools like SEToolkit and conceptual Wi-Fi cracking, it identifies exploitable weaknesses.Highlighting pathways for unauthorized access and potential data exfiltration.
Connected Pakistan Network Penetesting O.fileName: Connected Pakistan Network Penetesting Official Document 5_097873a7.pdf

Advanced Scan Connected Pakistan_Nessus.title: Nessus WebApp Pentesting Report
Advanced Scan Connected Pakistan_Nessus.description: This report presents the findings from a comprehensive vulnerability scan conducted using Nessus, an industry-leading and globally recognized tool. It details identified security weaknesses across network hosts and applications, leveraging its extensive vulnerability database.

Comprehensive Web Application Security A.title: Comprehensive WebApp PenTesting Report
Comprehensive Web Application Security A.description: This report details the comprehensive web application penetration test, leveraging a multi-tool approach. It integrates findings from our Custom Web Application, OWASP ZAP, Nessus, and Nikto scans. Applicable vulnerabilities were then meticulously analyzed to generate this detailed custom report. Providing tailored solutions and insights for significant web application security enhancement for Connected Pakistan.
Comprehensive Web Application Security A.fileName: Comprehensive Web Application Security Assessment Official Document 6_ad034143.pdf

Comprehensive Security Assessment Report.title: Security Audit Report (Final)
Comprehensive Security Assessment Report.description: This Final Comprehensive Security Audit Report consolidates all findings from the web application, network, configuration, and physical security assessments. It presents a holistic and integrated overview of the organization's entire security posture. Providing a definitive set of prioritized recommendations for strategic security enhancement and risk mitigation for Connected Pakistan
Comprehensive Security Assessment Report.fileName: Comprehensive Security Assessment Report Final Agreement_e157dfbc.pdf
